title: ADR-260 #7 — the thief's death raises the ceiling without moving the rank
story: dungeo
description: |
  Dungeo raises maxScore from 616 to 650 when the thief dies (ADR-078's hidden
  points, melee-interceptor.ts). Rank thresholds are ABSOLUTE POINTS, so that
  call must leave the player's rank exactly where it was. Under percentage
  bands it would silently DEMOTE a player who earned nothing and lost nothing —
  which is the whole reason ADR-260 D2 made thresholds absolute.

  Restores from wt-13, which is the chain state immediately after the fight.
---

# ============================================================================
# GOAL: the ceiling moved; the rank did not
# ============================================================================

[GOAL: Rank is unchanged across the 616 -> 650 ceiling change]

# State from the end of wt-13 — the thief is dead, so the ceiling has
# already risen to 650.
$restore wt-13

# The ledger is the single home for scoring (ADR-260 D1): SCORE reads it and
# nothing else. "Adventurer" is dungeo's own rank name — ported verbatim from
# ADR-085 — and appears in no platform source, which is what proves stdlib
# invented nothing (ADR-260 acceptance #3).
#
# The rank follows from the ABSOLUTE threshold: 400 <= 493 < 616 is
# "Adventurer", and it stays "Adventurer" whether the ceiling reads 616 or
# 650. A percentage ladder would have to recompute here, and 493/616 = 80%
# against 493/650 = 76% is exactly the kind of drift that silently re-ranks a
# player who did nothing.
> score
[OK: contains "493 out of 650"]
[OK: contains "rank of an Adventurer"]

# The five percentage-band ranks stdlib used to hardcode are gone (ADR-260 D4).
# If any of these appears, the deleted computeRank came back.
[OK: not contains "Novice"]
[OK: not contains "Proficient"]
[OK: not contains "Expert"]
[OK: not contains "Master"]

# Twice in a row: the rank is DERIVED from the ledger on every read, never
# stored, so two consecutive reads of an unchanged score agree exactly.
> score
[OK: contains "493 out of 650"]
[OK: contains "rank of an Adventurer"]

[END GOAL]
